3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Vertex calculates NEAR/USDT funding rates every hour using its on-chain risk engine combined with off-chain sequencer data. The hybrid architecture enables real-time mark price updates while maintaining decentralized settlement on Arbitrum. Cross-margin positions automatically optimize capital efficiency across all trading pairs. Funding payments occur precisely at each hour mark with sub-second execution through the sequencer."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","NEAR","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"NEAR's position as a Layer 1 blockchain creates periodic funding rate imbalances during network updates and ecosystem developments. The pair's mid-tier volume provides sufficient liquidity while avoiding the extreme competition seen in major pairs. NEAR's correlation with broader L1 narratives generates predictable funding patterns around sector rotations."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical NEAR Funding Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"NEAR/USDT funding rates on Vertex typically range from -0.05% to +0.15% hourly during normal market conditions. Ecosystem announcements around Aurora updates or NEAR Protocol developments often push rates above +0.20% as spot demand increases. During broader crypto sell-offs, NEAR futures trade at discounts with negative rates reaching -0.10% or lower. The hourly frequency creates 24 funding opportunities daily, allowing rapid position adjustments during volatile periods."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Cross-Margin Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Vertex's default cross-margin system enables efficient capital utilization for NEAR funding arbitrage strategies. Traders can hedge NEAR exposure through correlated L1 positions like APT or SUI without additional margin requirements. The platform's 0.02% maker rebate effectively reduces funding costs when entering positions. Fast sequencer execution allows precise entry timing around funding payments, maximizing capture efficiency."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"NEAR's mid-tier liquidity can create slippage during large position changes, especially around funding payment times. Vertex's concentration on Arbitrum creates bridge risk for funds entering the ecosystem. The sequencer's centralization introduces potential downtime risks during critical funding periods. NEAR's correlation with other L1 tokens can reduce hedge effectiveness during sector-wide moves, requiring careful position sizing."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does Vertex's hourly funding frequency affect NEAR arbitrage strategies?","answer":"Hourly funding provides 24 opportunities daily to capture rate changes, allowing more responsive positioning than 8-hour cycles. The frequent payments reduce overnight exposure risk but require active monitoring for optimal execution."},{"question":"What makes NEAR suitable for funding arbitrage on Vertex?","answer":"NEAR's L1 status creates periodic funding imbalances during ecosystem developments. The pair's mid-volume provides adequate liquidity while avoiding extreme competition from institutional arbitrageurs common in BTC/ETH pairs."},{"question":"How does cross-margin affect NEAR funding positions?","answer":"Cross-margin allows hedging NEAR exposure through correlated positions without additional capital. This improves capital efficiency but requires monitoring of portfolio-wide risk as all positions share margin requirements."},{"question":"What are the main risks of NEAR funding arbitrage on Vertex?","answer":"Key risks include NEAR's price volatility overwhelming funding gains, Arbitrum bridge delays affecting position management, and sequencer downtime during critical funding periods. Position sizing should account for these platform-specific factors."}]}]
